## Information Needed From IT / IAM

Ask IT/IAM to create or confirm an OIDC web application for this app.

Required from IT/IAM:

| Item | Needed Value |
| --- | --- |
| Client ID | Provider client ID |
| Client secret | Provider client secret |
| Issuer URL | Provider issuer URL |
| Assigned users/groups | Group or assignment list |
| App owner | Person/team responsible |
| Secret rotation owner | Person/team responsible |
| Production approval | Required before production use |

Recommended Okta redirect URI:

```text
https://<APP_HOST>/api/auth/callback/okta
```

Recommended local development redirect URI:

```text
http://localhost:3000/api/auth/callback/okta
```

Recommended sign-out URI:

```text
https://<APP_HOST>/login
```

Recommended scopes:

```text
openid profile email
```

## Environment Variables To Configure

Do not commit real values to Git.

| Variable | Required | Owner | Notes |
| --- | --- | --- | --- |
| AUTH_SECRET | Yes | App/deployment owner | Generate a strong random value. |
| NEXTAUTH_SECRET | Yes | App/deployment owner | Can match AUTH_SECRET if the app standard allows. |
| NEXTAUTH_URL | Yes | App/deployment owner | Must match deployed app origin. |
| OKTA_ENABLED | If using Okta | App/deployment owner | Usually true. |
| NEXT_PUBLIC_OKTA_ENABLED | If using Okta | App/deployment owner | Usually true; controls login button visibility. |
| OKTA_CLIENT_ID | If using Okta | IT/IAM | From Okta OIDC app. |
| OKTA_CLIENT_SECRET | If using Okta | IT/IAM | Secret value from Okta. |
| OKTA_ISSUER | If using Okta | IT/IAM | Example: https://your-org.okta.com |
| AUTH0_ENABLED | If using Auth0 | App/deployment owner | Usually true. |
| NEXT_PUBLIC_AUTH0_ENABLED | If using Auth0 | App/deployment owner | Usually true; controls login button visibility. |
| AUTH0_CLIENT_ID | If using Auth0 | IT/IAM | From Auth0 application. |
| AUTH0_CLIENT_SECRET | If using Auth0 | IT/IAM | Secret value from Auth0. |
| AUTH0_ISSUER | If using Auth0 | IT/IAM | Auth0 issuer URL. |

Generate a local secret with:

```bash
openssl rand -base64 32
```

